{"title_page": "James Macdonell (journalist)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2012}}\n\n'''James Macdonell''' (1841 &ndash; 2 March 1879) was a Scottish journalist.\n\n==Life==\nMacdonell was born at [[Dyce]] near [[Aberdeen]]. In 1858, after his father's death, he became clerk in a merchant's office. He began writing in the ''Aberdeen Free Press''; in 1862 he was appointed to the staff of the ''Daily Review'' in [[Edinburgh]], and at 22 he became editor of the ''Northern Daily Express''.\n\nIn 1865 Macdonell went to London with a staff position on the ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'', which he held until 1875,  as special correspondent in France in 1870 and 1871. In 1873 he became a leader-writer on ''[[The Times]].'' He died in London on 2 March 1879. His posthumous ''France since the First Empire'', though incomplete, gave insights into the French politics of his time.\n\n==References==\n*{{EB1911|wstitle=Macdonell, James|volume=17|page=213}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=James Macdonell |birth=1841 |death=1879 |sopt=t}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macdonell, James}}\n[[Category:1841 births]]\n[[Category:1879 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Scottish journalists]]\n[[Category:19th-century journalists]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:19th-century British male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2012}}\n\n'''James Macdonell''' (1841 &ndash; 2 March 1879) was a Scottish journalist.\n\n==Life==\nMacdonell was born at [[Dyce]] near [[Aberdeen]]. In 1858, after his father's death, he became clerk in a merchant's office. He began writing in the ''Aberdeen Free Press''; in 1862 he was appointed to the staff of the ''Daily Review'' in [[Edinburgh]], and at 22 he became editor of the ''Northern Daily Express''.\n\nIn 1865 Macdonell went to London with a staff position on the ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'', which he held until 1875,  as special correspondent in France in 1870 and 1871. In 1873 he became a leader-writer on ''[[The Times]].'' He died in London on 2 March 1879. His posthumous ''France since the First Empire'', though incomplete, gave insights into the French politics of his time.\n\n==References==\n*{{EB1911|wstitle=Macdonell, James|volume=17|page=213}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=James Macdonell |birth=1841 |death=1879 |sopt=t}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Macdonell, James}}\n[[Category:1841 births]]\n[[Category:1879 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Scottish journalists]]\n[[Category:19th-century journalists]]\n[[Category:British male journalists]]\n[[Category:19th-century British male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Macdonell_(journalist)"}
{"title_page": "2013 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division C", "text_new": "{{Infobox international basketball competition\n| logo         =\n| size         =\n| country      = [[Andorra]]\n| city         = [[Andorra la Vella]]\n| dates        = 15\u201320 July 2013\n| num_teams    = 6\n| confederations = 1\n| champion_other = {{bku|18|SMR}}\n| count        = 1\n| second_other = {{bku|18|MDA}}\n| third_other  = {{bku|18|AND}}\n| prevseason   = [[2011 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division C|2011]]\n| nextseason   = [[2014 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division C|2014]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2013 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division C''' was the 9th edition of the Division C of the [[FIBA U18 European Championship]], the third tier of the European men's under-18 [[basketball]] championship. It was played in [[Andorra la Vella]], [[Andorra]], from 15 to 20 July 2013.<ref>[http://www.fiba.basketball/pages/eng/fa/event/p/cid//sid/9481/_/2013_U18_European_Championship_Men_Division_C_/index.html FIBA Archive]</ref> [[San Marino men's national under-18 basketball team]] won the tournament.\n\n==Participating teams==\n*{{bku|18|AND}}\n*{{bku|18|GIB}}\n*{{bku|18|MDA}}\n*{{bku|18|MON}}\n*{{bku|18|SMR}}\n*{{bku|18|WAL}}\n\n==First round==\n===Group A===\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WL\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://www.fiba.basketball/pages/eng/fa/event/p/sid/9481/_/2013_U18_European_Championship_Men_Division_C_/group-standing.html FIBA Archive]\n|for_against_style=points |winpoints=2|losspoints=1\n\n|team1=MDA|team2=SMR|team3=WAL\n\n|win_MDA=2|loss_MDA=0|gf_MDA=173|ga_MDA=137\n|win_SMR=1|loss_SMR=1|gf_SMR=132|ga_SMR=152\n|win_WAL=0|loss_WAL=2|gf_WAL=144|ga_WAL=160\n\n|name_MDA={{bku|18|MDA}}\n|name_SMR={{bku|18|SMR}}\n|name_WAL={{bku|18|WAL}}\n\n|result1=SF |result2=QF |result3=QF\n|res_col_header=Q\n|col_SF=green1|text_SF=Semifinals\n|col_QF=blue1|text_QF=Quarterfinals\n}}\n\n===Group B===\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WL\n|update=complete\n|source=